                  </persName>
             sworn. - I am a constable,(produces the property;) I have had them ever since, I received them from Mrs. Weston.</p>
               <p>Mrs. Weston. I received this cloak and apron from Simpson, and gave them to the officer; they are my property, I had seen them ten minutes before.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's defence. I had come three hundred miles, with three fatherless children, and buried one on the road; I was very sack and fatigued; I went into this house and sat down, and slept about half an hour; I did not know that I had the things till I saw them at my feet, when he stopped me.</p>
               <p>GUILTY (Aged 41.)</p>

